I’m checking reliable sources for how to frame the exhibitions section so the page copy stays grounded and clean. Then I’ll draft the full landing page HTML for /exhibitions/index.html.

I found enough to support the core framing: Ron English has a documented record of both solo exhibitions and group exhibitions, and gallery records plus exhibition databases consistently separate those two categories. 

I’m turning that into a simple exhibitions landing page with two entry cards, brief orientation text, and paths that fit /exhibitions/index.html.

Thought for 48s
This structure makes sense. A clean exhibitions hub with two cards is the right move, and the safest verified language is to frame it around documented solo exhibitions and documented group exhibitions, since r
nctions. 

Because this page will live at ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/, I adjusted the relative paths like this:

stylesheet: ../css/styles.css

catalogue home: ../index.html

main site: ../../index.html

images: ../images/exhibitions/...

subpages: solo/index.html and group/index.html

Here is a full draft for ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/index.html:

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Exhibitions | Ron English Catalogue Raisonné</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/styles.css" />

  <style>
    :root{
      --border:#e5e7eb;
      --muted:#4b5563;
      --shadow:0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.08);
      --radius:18px;
      --bg:#ffffff;
      --panel:#f8fafc;
    }

    *{
      box-sizing:border-box;
    }

    body{
      margin:0;
      font-family:system-ui,-apple-system,Segoe UI,Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;
      color:#111;
      background:var(--bg);
    }

    .wrap{
      max-width:1100px;
      margin:0 auto;
      padding:28px 18px 60px;
    }

    .nav-pills{
      display:flex;
      flex-wrap:wrap;
      gap:10px;
      margin-bottom:22px;
    }

    .nav-pill{
      padding:8px 14px;
      border-radius:999px;
      border:1px solid #d6e1ff;
      background:#fff;
      color:#111;
      text-decoration:none;
      font-size:14px;
    }

    .nav-pill:hover{
      background:#f3f6ff;
    }

    h1{
      font-size:clamp(36px,5vw,62px);
      margin:0 0 10px;
      letter-spacing:-.02em;
    }

    .subtitle{
      font-size:18px;
      line-height:1.55;
      color:var(--muted);
      max-width:72ch;
      margin:0;
    }

    .intro{
      margin-top:24px;
      padding:18px 20px;
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius:var(--radius);
      background:var(--panel);
    }

    .intro p{
      margin:0;
      font-size:16px;
      line-height:1.65;
      color:#1f2937;
      max-width:75ch;
    }

    .entry-grid{
      margin-top:28px;
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr));
      gap:20px;
    }

    .entry{
      display:block;
      border:1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius:var(--radius);
      overflow:hidden;
      box-shadow:var(--shadow);
      text-decoration:none;
      color:inherit;
      background:#fff;
      transition:transform .12s ease, box-shadow .12s ease;
    }

    .entry:hover{
      transform:translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow:0 16px 40px rgba(0,0,0,.12);
    }

    .entry img{
      width:100%;
      height:300px;
      object-fit:cover;
      display:block;
      background:#f3f4f6;
    }

    .entry-body{
      padding:18px 18px 20px;
    }

    .eyebrow{
      display:inline-block;
      margin-bottom:8px;
      font-size:12px;
      font-weight:700;
      letter-spacing:.08em;
      text-transform:uppercase;
      color:#6b7280;
    }

    .entry h2{
      margin:0 0 8px;
      font-size:26px;
      line-height:1.15;
    }

    .entry p{
      margin:0;
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:16px;
      line-height:1.6;
      max-width:58ch;
    }

    .cta{
      margin-top:14px;
      display:flex;
      align-items:center;
      gap:10px;
      font-weight:650;
      color:#111;
    }

    .dot{
      width:10px;
      height:10px;
      border-radius:999px;
      background:#111;
      display:inline-block;
      flex:0 0 auto;
    }

    .notes{
      margin-top:28px;
      padding:20px;
      border-top:1px solid var(--border);
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:15px;
      line-height:1.65;
    }

    .notes strong{
      color:#111;
    }

    footer{
      margin-top:30px;
      padding-top:16px;
      border-top:1px solid var(--border);
      color:var(--muted);
      font-size:14px;
    }

    @media (max-width:900px){
      .entry-grid{
        grid-template-columns:1fr;
      }

      .entry img{
        height:260px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <main class="wrap">
    <nav class="nav-pills" aria-label="Site navigation">
      <a class="nav-pill" href="../../index.html">Main site</a>
      <a class="nav-pill" href="../index.html">Catalogue home</a>
    </nav>

    <header>
      <h1>Exhibitions</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        A guide to documented exhibitions featuring Ron English’s work, divided into solo exhibitions and group exhibitions for easier browsing and long-term reference.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="intro" aria-label="About this section">
      <p>
        This section separates exhibitions into two paths. Solo exhibitions focus on shows centered on Ron English’s work, while group exhibitions document broader presentations in which his work appeared alongside other artists. Listings can be organized year by year, with venue, city, and dates included when documented.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="entry-grid" aria-label="Exhibition navigation">

      <a class="entry" href="solo/index.html">
        <img src="../images/exhibitions/solo-square.jpg" alt="Ron English solo exhibitions">
        <div class="entry-body">
          <span class="eyebrow">Exhibition history</span>
          <h2>Solo Exhibitions</h2>
          <p>
            Exhibitions devoted to Ron English’s work, organized for clear chronological reference and citation.
          </p>
          <div class="cta">
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span>Enter solo exhibitions</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a class="entry" href="group/index.html">
        <img src="../images/exhibitions/group-square.jpg" alt="Ron English group exhibitions">
        <div class="entry-body">
          <span class="eyebrow">Exhibition history</span>
          <h2>Group Exhibitions</h2>
          <p>
            Group shows, themed exhibitions, and other multi-artist presentations in which Ron English’s work was included.
          </p>
          <div class="cta">
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <span>Enter group exhibitions</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

    </section>

    <section class="notes" aria-label="Editorial note">
      <strong>Editorial note:</strong> Exhibition entries may include title, venue, city, date range, and supporting documentation as available.
    </section>

    <footer>
      Published via GitHub Pages for long-term public access.
    </footer>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
A few design choices here are doing useful work:

The title becomes just Exhibitions, which keeps it cleaner and lets the subtitle carry the detail.

The short intro gives visitors immediate orientation, so they know what the difference is between solo and group pages.

The “organized year by year, with venue, city, and dates included when documented” line is a sound editorial statement about how you are structuring the archive, not a claim about Ron’s whole exhibition record.

The relative links should work correctly from inside /exhibitions/.

The underlying distinction between solo and group exhibitions is well supported by exhibition records and gallery materials for Ron English. 

Next, I’d recommend that the solo and group subpages use the same visual system so the section feels unified.


