The main problem is almost certainly the folder or file name does not match the link exactly.

You linked to:

href="exhibitions/index.html"
From your main page at:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/index.html
that means GitHub Pages will look for:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/index.html
But you wrote the exhibitions page location as:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonee/exhibitions/index
I see at least two likely issues there.

First, raisonee is spelled differently from raisonne.

Second, index may not actually be index.html.

GitHub Pages needs the path to match exactly. So this is what you should confirm:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/
  index.html
  exhibitions/
    index.html
And your images should be here:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/
  images/
    exhibitions/
      exhibitions.jpg
      exhibitions-hero.jpg
      group-square.jpg
      solo-square.jpg
The fix is this:

Your folder name must be:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne
not:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonee
Your exhibitions page file must be named:

index.html
not just index.

Your main-page card link should stay:

<a class="entry" href="exhibitions/index.html">
That part is correct if the folder and filename are correct.

There are also a couple of path issues inside the exhibitions page itself.

Because this page lives at:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/index.html
these links should be:

<a class="nav-pill" href="../index.html">Catalogue home</a>
That one is correct.

But this one:

<a class="nav-pill" href="../../index.html">Main site</a>
is only correct if you truly have a site above ron-english-catalogue-raisonne. If not, it is wrong.

If your catalogue itself is the site root, then change it to:

<a class="nav-pill" href="../index.html">Main site</a>
If you want both pills, one could go to the site root and one to the catalogue home, but in your current structure those may actually be the same page.

Also, your image paths on the exhibitions page are correct only if the images are really here:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/images/exhibitions/
Then these are fine:

<img src="../images/exhibitions/exhibitions-hero.jpg" alt="Ron English solo exhibitions">
<img src="../images/exhibitions/group-square.jpg" alt="Ron English group exhibitions">
So the most likely repair checklist is:

Rename the repo folder or folder in your local project so it is always ron-english-catalogue-raisonne.

Make sure the exhibitions page is exactly exhibitions/index.html.

Make sure capitalization matches exactly. GitHub Pages is case-sensitive.

Re-upload or commit the corrected file structure.

Keep the main-page exhibitions card as:

href="exhibitions/index.html"
Here is the clean version of the link block from your main page, which is fine as written:

<a class="entry" href="exhibitions/index.html">
  <img src="images/exhibitions/exhibitions.jpg" alt="Exhibitions featuring works by Ron English">
  <div class="entry-body">
    <h2>Exhibitions</h2>
    <p>Selected solo and group exhibitions documenting the public presentation of Ron English’s work.</p>
    <div class="cta"><span class="dot"></span><span>Enter exhibitions</span></div>
  </div>
</a>
And here is the only part of the exhibitions page I would change right away if the catalogue is the root site:

<nav class="nav-pills" aria-label="Site navigation">
  <a class="nav-pill" href="../index.html">Main site</a>
  <a class="nav-pill" href="../index.html">Catalogue home</a>
</nav>
or just simplify it to one pill:

<nav class="nav-pills" aria-label="Site navigation">
