I also normalized a few date formats from the source so the table reads like the others, such as 1 June – 31 December 2020 to June 1 – December 31, 2020, and February 16–23, 2022 to February 16 – 23, 2022. 
2020s-group-exhibitions


At this point, your full solo and group exhibition section has a consistent structure. The next useful cleanup would be a pass on the detail-page folders and link naming so every decade page points to one naming system.


Sources

now i need for each table entry in each main decade or half decade page for exhibitions to go to an individual page that has info about that particlualr exphibition, so first let's work on ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/solo
/1970s-1980s-solo-exhibitions.html
first tell me whwere should the pages for these live so i can make a dedicated folder? then we'll go from there. 

Thought for a second
The cleanest place is inside the same section folder, in a dedicated subfolder named for that page.

So for this page:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/solo/1970s-1980s-solo-exhibitions.html
the individual exhibition pages should live here:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/solo/1970s-1980s-solo-shows/
That gives you this structure:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/
  exhibitions/
    solo/
      index.html
      1970s-1980s-solo-exhibitions.html
      1990s-solo-exhibitions.html
      2000s-solo-exhibitions.html
      2010s-solo-exhibitions.html
      2020s-solo-exhibitions.html
      1970s-1980s-solo-shows/
        annus-mirabilis-kwikwash-gallery-1980.html
        beyond-the-groovy-planet-levlowe-gallery-1980.html
        showflaps-billboards-indoors-outdoors-fashion-moda-1986.html
        photographs-midtown-y-photography-gallery-1988.html
        ron-english-fotogalerie-prinsengracht-356-1988.html
        ron-english-ok-harris-works-of-art-1989.html
That is the best pattern because:

It keeps each decade page next to its detail-page folder.

The relative links stay simple.

You can repeat the same system for every other decade.

So later you would also have:

exhibitions/solo/1990s-solo-shows/
exhibitions/solo/2000s-solo-shows/
exhibitions/solo/2010s-solo-shows/
exhibitions/solo/2020s-solo-shows/
and for group:

exhibitions/group/1980s-group-shows/
exhibitions/group/1990s-group-shows/
exhibitions/group/2000-2004-group-shows/
exhibitions/group/2005-2009-group-shows/
exhibitions/group/2010-2014-group-shows/
exhibitions/group/2015-2019-group-shows/
exhibitions/group/2020s-group-shows/
One important note: in some of the earlier code blocks, a few links were pointing to folder names like 2000s-group-exhibitions/ instead of 2000s-group-shows/. I would strongly recommend standardizing all detail-page folders to *-solo-shows and *-group-shows so the naming stays consistent.

For the page you asked about, create this folder now:

ron-english-catalogue-raisonne/exhibitions/solo/1970s-1980s-solo-shows/
Then each row in 1970s-1980s-solo-exhibitions.html should link into that folder with paths like:

href="1970s-1980s-solo-shows/annus-mirabilis-kwikwash-gallery-1980.html"
That part is already the right pattern.



